\enumerate{
\item aligns \code{init_data} and \code{cand_data} by \code{id_col};
\item optionally flips traits in \code{lower_is_better} so all objectives are in
the same direction;
\item optionally scales traits using \code{ref_data};
\item computes a phenotypic correlation matrix \code{P} and a genetic covariance
matrix \code{G};
\item repeatedly samples candidate desired-gain vectors, computes index
coefficients, evaluates realized gains on the selected set, and keeps
the best solution according to a goodness-of-fit criterion.
